## Example Scenarios (Generic Walkthrough)

### Scenario 1: User says "Start refactoring the product details page"

```text
Phase 1 Gathering (AI Parallel Execution):
  - Hook Sniffing: Detected .cursor/rules/project-playbook.mdc, read project paths and component constraints
  - Historical Convos: Searched "product details" → Found 4 relevant convos
  - Relevant Docs: docs/design/Product_Details_Design.md §2.1
  - Existing Rules: Hit p1-frontend-components.mdc
  - Code Dependencies: Relevant modules in src/components/Product/
  - Recent Changes: Relevant commits in git log

Phase 2 Summary (AI Presents):
  → Structured summary, referencing design scheme §2.1

Phase 3 Confirmation (Human Decision):
  → User confirms: "Do the core purchase button area first"

Phase 4a (Human Selection): Path A - Needs deep design
Phase 4b (State Transition): User says "A, discuss button state logic first" → Conditional confirmation
Phase 4c (AI advances brainstorming, Human drives discussion):
  → brainstorming discusses out-of-stock, pre-order, normal purchase states
  → Detected frontend task → Auto-load frontend-design + ui-ux-pro-max
  → User says "Scheme is set" → brainstorming exit signal
  → AI prompts "Enter Path B?" → User confirms → Enter 4c implementation chain
  → Load p1-frontend-components.mdc rule to execute
```

### Scenario 2: User says "Continue debugging the payment module from last time"

```text
Phase 1 Gathering (AI Parallel Execution):
  - Historical Convos: Found troubleshooting progress of Webhook signature verification from last time
  - Existing Rules: Hit payment-security.mdc

Phase 2 Summary (AI Presents):
  → Last progress, pending items, test conclusions

Phase 3 Confirmation (Human Decision):
  → User confirms: "Continue from the signature 401 error"

Phase 4a (Human Selection): Path D - Debugging/Troubleshooting
Phase 4b (State Transition): User says "D, check again as discussed last time" → Confirmation signal
Phase 4c (AI Autonomous Advancement):
  → Load payment-security.mdc
  → systematic-debugging four-phase troubleshooting
  → verification-before-completion verify results
  → Report test conclusions
```

### Scenario 3: User says "Add a new report export feature"

```text
Phase 1-3 (Human Driven):
  → Gather data structure design docs, existing report code structure
  → User confirms requirements and constraints

Phase 4a (Human Selection): Path B - Scheme clear, needs implementation plan
Phase 4b (State Transition): User says "Select B, start" → Confirmation signal
Phase 4c (AI Full-chain Autonomous Advancement):
  → writing-plans breaks down into 8 bite-sized tasks
  → Detected Excel gen/edit involved → Auto-load xlsx skill
  → test-driven-development write generation logic tests first
  → subagent-driven-development parallel execution
  → requesting-code-review after every 3 tasks
  → verification-before-completion full test
  → finishing-a-development-branch commit/PR
```